  "body": "Like other apps (sushi, uniswap etc) if you have some pending transactions its useful to see if those transactions have reverted/committed onto the network.\n\nThis UX element would allow you to see the list of pending transactions the dashboard has sent out to the provider.\n\nThere would be a hook on the provider for that tx to show the result once its async callback/event has triggered.\n\nUsually there is a modal/hover over with the tx and a link to the block explorer:\n\n![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/6237b50f8a17541a8eeade42/de5b80e7-9502-426b-9faf-03d1a3b4f1db)\n\nThere is also a list against the top view of the address:\n\n![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/6237b50f8a17541a8eeade42/c0241439-2cff-4679-97bd-d20c8ba57593)\n\nThey drive this via a redux instance but for use it might be ok to start with a simple state collection as we are really a single page app right now.\n\nIf we were to change to multiple pages, then redux for state might be better.\n\n",
